Check any update .sh file is present or not in the directory
			-ll

			if it is present then run the file ----> sudo ./{filename}.sh

check any update .txt file is present or not in the directory
			-ll

			if it is present then run the file ----> pip install -r {filename}.txt

check any update .py file is present or not in the directory
            -ll

            if it is present then run the file ----> python3 {filename}.py

